    "feat": {
        "name": "Pirate Dedication",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "As a pirate, you sail the seas in search of enemy ships to plunder and great adventures to embark on. You gain the Additional Lore general feat for Sailing Lore or for a specific coastal city you have a connection to (such as Port Peril Lore). You ignore the effects of difficult terrain or uneven ground caused by unstable ground (such as the deck of a ship). Additionally, you gain the Boarding Assault action.   \n  \n **Boarding Assault** (flourish) Either Stride twice or attempt an Acrobatics check (DC determined by the GM, but usually DC 20) to swing up to twice your Speed on a rope or similar object, then Strike. If you boarded or disembarked from a boat or similar vehicle during this movement, the Strike deals one additional weapon damage die.",
        "level": 2,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Archetype",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 12,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
